804-808 (old Nos. 454-458) Sixth Ave., east side, between West 27th and 28th Streets. The centre portion of building (Moquins Restaurant) is a

Brown Brothers.

709407f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 27th Street, showing same before and after the demolition of the old "gg" structure. The station seen is at 28th Sgreet. Note the streetcar under same. These were removed and transportation is now provided for by buses. The later view has the towering Empite State Building in
its background.
January 29, 1928
March 29, 1939
P. L. Sperr
The samme as above, from another angle.
P. L. Sperr  September 27, 1940
